The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 February is 39,599 (4,583.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 February, there were 762 new confirmed cases (88.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 February, there were 1,120 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (358 fewer cases).
